# Coding Standards

Canonical shared rules source: `/home/caraxes/.dev-rules.md`

## Python
- Python 3.13+ with modern syntax (match/case, `X | Y` unions)
- **Formatter**: ruff only (not black, isort, pylint)
- **Line length**: 120 characters
- **Type hints**: required on all function signatures
- **Logging**: structlog — no bare `print()` in production code
- **Data models**: Pydantic v2 (`model_validator`, not `@validator`)
- **Package manager**: `uv` exclusively — never bare `python` or `pip`
- **Prohibited**: `eval()`, `exec()`, `pickle`

## TypeScript
- Strict mode, ESLint + Prettier
- Named exports preferred over default exports

## File Standards
- **Line endings**: LF (`\n`), not CRLF
- **Trailing whitespace**: trim on save
- **Final newline**: insert on save

## Commits
- Conventional format: `feat(scope):`, `fix(scope):`, `test(scope):`, `docs(scope):`
- One commit, one concern

## Package Managers
- Python → `uv`
- CascadeProjects MCP servers → `npm`
- mcp-tool-experiment → `pnpm`

## Safety-Critical Code
- Never weaken validation in `safety/`, `security/`, `boundaries/`
- Never add bypass paths or dev-mode shortcuts
- Always maintain audit trail integrity
- Local-first AI: Ollama + ChromaDB (no external APIs unless asked)
